    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 7000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - CLEARANCE LIGHT / DIRECTIONAL LIGHT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CLEARANCE LIGHT / DIRECTIONAL LIGHT</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Clearance Light / Directional Light- Removal</title>
            <para>The clearance light is located at the rear of the fender hood section above the hood latching
                mechanism.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the clearance light assembly plug.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Twist bulb assembly and remove socket from clearance light assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove Phillips head screw on outboard side of housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove torque head screw at back section of housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clearance light assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow same procedure for removal of opposite side clearance light.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0900741" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900741.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Clearance Lights or Optional Directional Lights</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER MOUNTED CLEARANCE LIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING HOLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. FENDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MOUNTING GASKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MOUNTING LOCK WASHERS</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. MOUNTING NUTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. DIRECTIONAL LIGHT FENDER SPACER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. DIRECTIONAL LIGHT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Clearance Light / Directional Light - Install</title>
            <para>With hood tilted insert the clearance light or directional light assembly into the clearance light
                housing in the mounting hole in the top fender section. (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900741">Figure 41, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align and insert light assembly in the mounting holes in fender section.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert Phillips head screw in outboard mounting hole and tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place bulb and socket assembly in clearance light assembly and twist to lock.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Plug harness into headlight assembly harness.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
